Package com.example.syntaxeventlottery

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.example.syntaxeventlottery.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Event extends Object implements Serializable
The Event class represents an event in the Event Lottery System. It includes details about the event such as its name, description, capacity, participants, and organizer information. It also manages functionality for waiting lists, confirmed participants, and geolocation requirements.

      public Event(String eventName, String facilityName, String facilityLocation, String description, int capacity, Date startDate, Date endDate, String organizerId, Integer waitingListLimit, boolean locationRequired)
      Parameterized constructor to create an Event with specific details.
      Parameters:
      eventName - Name of the event.
      description - Description of the event.
      capacity - Maximum capacity of participants.
      startDate - Start date and time of the event.
      endDate - End date and time of the event.
      organizerId - ID of the organizer creating the event.
      waitingListLimit - Limit of the waiting list (i.e., participants list). No limit if null
